The paper deals with routing schemes and distance oracles in graphs, which are fundamental topics in computer science and fall under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the space and header requirements for these schemes, which are relevant to network protocols and communication systems (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper uses techniques from information theory (cs.IT) and algorithm design (cs.AL) to develop and analyze the routing schemes. Finally, the paper presents applications of the routing schemes, such as in distributed computing and network optimization, which could potentially fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SI).
